Problem: how can we find the global optimal path?
Although we know distance between connected nodes, we have to try every path to find out the shortest path, which cost a lot of time. (If you find the best path without exploring the whole map, you are lucky. And how can you guarantee that?)


Solve: If we have some knowledge between nodes that are not directly connected,  AND we are OK with a good path (not the best but not too bad). We can use the knowledge to trade for the searching time. (Time Vs. Optimal)


